The paper deals with measuring the intelligence of agents in reward-giving environments, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves comparing the relative intelligence of two agents, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of ultrafilters and structural theorems suggests a mathematical approach, which could be classified under information theory (cs.IT) or mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with comparing and evaluating agents, which could also be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
